### Q37: Explain the Fork/Join Framework
**A:** Parallel processing framework (Java 7+). Uses work-stealing algorithm.

```java
class SumTask extends RecursiveTask<Integer> {
    int[] arr; int lo, hi;
    SumTask(int[] a, int l, int h) { arr = a; lo = l; hi = h; }
    protected Integer compute() {
        if (hi - lo < 1000) return IntStream.range(lo, hi).map(i -> arr[i]).sum();
        int mid = (lo + hi) / 2;
        SumTask left = new SumTask(arr, lo, mid);
        SumTask right = new SumTask(arr, mid, hi);
        left.fork();
        return right.compute() + left.join();
    }
}
// ForkJoinPool.commonPool().invoke(new SumTask(arr, 0, arr.length));
```

